This paper deals with the capacity region of bidirectional relay networks, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of lattice codes and interference cancelation, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves communication engineering (cs.CE) concepts such as channel models and capacity regions. Finally, the paper discusses the use of relay nodes, which is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI).
